greedy when it comes to shiny things. As such, it’s a sign that a Meowth...
body:
Meowth have a not-undeserved reputation for being greedy when it comes to shiny things. As such, it’s a sign that a Meowth really likes their trainer if they gift them something from their collection, even if it’s a “lesser” present like tin foil or play money rather than real coins or jewelry. Superstition holds that keeping that gift with you at all times will bring wealth and good luck.

(requested by anonymous)

blog.name: friendsafariserver
blog.title: Friend Safari!
blog.description:
Friend Safari is a SFW, OC-friendly, paragraph-style roleplay server for main series Pokémon games. From Kanto to Alola, the whole Pokémon world is your Cloyster! Members of this server are allowed a total of four played characters, with at least one required to be canonical.

The server is run by a team of five mods who you can learn more about via the mods page. We cultivate an easygoing and open atmosphere, with member comfort and happiness being our top priority.

All of the links are in the drop down menu under Rowlet, labeled Pokémon! Hovering over each Pokémon will tell you what page they link to!

summary: Mika waddles up, bumping into Celodia's leg. Seems they were eavesdropping. "So? Do you have a lead to help that goopy thing?"
question: Mika waddles up, bumping into Celodia's leg. Seems they were eavesdropping. "So? Do you have a lead to help that goopy thing?"
answer:
“C’mon, Anthony. We gotta go find Jericho.”

“OKAY!”

They made the trip down the stairs after carefully locking the door. They made sure Mika was with them, too.

“Huh? Oh, there ya are, honey. Was beginnin’ t’think ya died up there. You been in there for hours seein’ visitors. Yer friend famous ‘r somethin’?”

“I… guess…?”

“Anyway, jus’ gimme a minute here ‘n’ we’ll patch up yer hand real good.”

Meanwhile, in the other side of the Saloon…

Celosia turned back at Anthony’s outburst.

“What, you see somethin’?”

“I know someone, I think. I go ask him things, I think.”

“Well, alright. I’ll be here ‘f you need me, okay? Don’t eat anyone.”

“YES!” 

As the Gothitelle left, The Ravener also exited the building too…

Eddie looked perplexed.

“Did’ja just tell ya friend not to eat anyone…?”

“It’s a long story. I’ll tell you in the back.”

“Alrigh’, alrigh’. C’mon back, dear.”

> FOLLOW RAVENER OR FOLLOW CELOSIA?
